I initiated and led design work for the CLO program, collaborating with stakeholders to shape a scalable solution. Although the program did not proceed due to budget constraints, I ensured that the design outputs remained well-documented and reusable. I then shifted to supporting the rebuild in the new technology stack, adapting quickly and contributing technically where needed.

I also played an active role in project planning, working closely with lead BAs and lead QAs to define a strategic roadmap for LoansHub for the year. This included effort estimation, sequencing of work items, and ensuring alignment between development capacity and business priorities.

Overall, I consistently upheld high engineering standards, encouraged knowledge sharing, strengthened team capability, and maintained transparent collaboration with cross-functional partners.


